content.description: A variation of Hexed. Once you lead Hexed, you can use Hex's anchors to climb this variation TR. To start, start out right where the udercling crack begins. Start traversing this crack left until it joins Hexed above.
content.location: Right of Hexed on the open-book dihedral with short crack.

content.description: The holds on this one are large and really fun. Great route for beginner climbers.
content.protection: 4 bolts to sport anchors. Use the right of the two belay stations.

content.description: The crux is right below the anchors.
content.protection: 5 bolts to sport anchors. Shares bolts 1 and 2 with Carnival and Living on the Edge. Use the left belay station.

content.description: It's an okay route. Just a little warm-up before hitting up Carnival just next door. Really short. Maybe the top makes it a 5.10b as rated.
content.protection: 5 bolts with sport clip anchors. Shares bolts 1 and 2 with Living on the Edge. Shares bolts 1 - 3 with Carnival. Use the left belay station.
content.location: First route on Gypsy Wall. Shares start with Carnival route.

content.description: This was North Shore's First bolted route.   PG Rated because of dead tree.
content.location: Mild dihedral with a full-cliff right facing crack before Gypsy wall

content.description: Shares same bolt line as Hexed, but you climb the flake to the right side and climb three feet to the right of anchors...avoid the 5.10 finish,
content.location: Open dihedral on little gypsy wall.

content.description:
Fun route. Some flat ledges down low and crimps and side pulls up higher. Staying to one side or the other can change the feel of the route a bit.

 May not be the first group to actually climb it, but no one else has bothered adding it to MP. So whatever, here it is, enjoy.
content.location:
The arete and shallow dihedral to the left of Gypsy's Magic. Set a TR by climbing Gypsy's Magic then traversing left past a few small dead-ish trees, a maybe solid rock you could thread a double length sling through to protect the traverse, and finally building an anchor on the solid tree using a long sling or cordellette.

 Please be careful on the traverse, protect it, a fall would be really bad.

 Clean by rapping off the tree or traversing back to Gypsy's Magic.

content.description: Mostly secluded. All the routes are up on a ledge 1 wall down from Mossy Wall.
